	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 1st 12:48 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=106600><span id=Scholar>Kamgar</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>242 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.26]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>There are at least two situations where Paladins can obtain the Twisted Silver Torque.<br><br>First, many Paladins wait to complete the Soulfire quest until it becomes necessary as a part of their epic. Nearly all Paladins will already have a weapon substantially better than Soulfire. Since it's not needed as a weapon, there's little reason to become KOS to the Freeport Militia until Soulfire is needed as a part of the Paladin epic.<br><br>Second, some Paladins save up Left Goblin Ears from Highpass so that they can fix their Freeport Militia faction after completing the Soulfire quest. The Twisted Silver Torque quest can be done with &quot;dubious&quot; Freeport Militia faction.<br><br>Kamgar<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
